cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS

The paper proposes a steganographic method for the P2P file sharing service BitTorrent, which involves modifying the order of data packets in the peer-peer data exchange protocol. This falls under the category of network security and cryptography, which is covered by cs.CR. Additionally, the paper involves experimental results acquired from a prototype implementation, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) as it deals with the peer-peer data exchange protocol used in BitTorrent.
